sections.heading: election, defined.Special election shall mean an election other than a regularly scheduled primary or general election as specified in statute or by home rule charter
sections.text: SourceLaws 1997, LB 764, ยง 12.AnnotationsSpecial election is defined by this section. Arends v. Whitten, 172 Neb. 297, 109 N.W.2d 363
